title: Sydney weather
text: Lower Western Sydney Forecast Saturday Very hot. Partly cloudy. Winds E/NE 15 to 25 km/h ahead of a S/SE change 20 to 30 km/h in the evening, reaching 30 to 45 km/h near the coast. Partly cloudy. High (80%) chance of showers. Light winds becoming SE/SW 20 to 30 km/h during the day. Sunday Hot. Partly cloudy. Slight (30%) chance of a shower in the afternoon and early evening. Winds S/SE 15 to 20 km/h tending N/NW in the W in the morning then tending S 25 to 40 km/h throughout in the middle of the day. Sun protection 9:10am to 5:20pm, UV Index predicted to reach 14 [Extreme]. Monday Mostly sunny day. Medium (50%) chance of showers in the evening. Winds S 15 to 20 km/h becoming light before dawn then becoming E/SE 15 to 20 km/h in the early afternoon. Tuesday Cloudy. Medium (60%) chance of showers, most likely in the morning and afternoon. Winds SE 15 to 20 km/h turning S 20 to 30 km/h during the morning then becoming S/SE and light during the evening. Wednesday Partly cloudy. Light winds becoming N 15 to 20 km/h during the day then tending NE 20 to 30 km/h during the afternoon. Issued Sat 16:20 EDT
